        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:44PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rutland, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pomeroy, Rutland, Forked Run State Park, Mason, Middleport, Chester,
Syracuse, and Dexter.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
